member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.PresentationFileType.Pps
member.summary: PPS, PowerPoint Slide Show, files are created using Microsoft PowerPoint for Slide Show purpose. PPS file reading and creation is supported by Microsoft PowerPoint 97-2003. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.PresentationFileType.Pptx
member.summary: Files with PPTX extension are presentation files created with popular Microsoft PowerPoint application. member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.PresentationFileType.Ppsx
member.summary: PPSX, Power Point Slide Show, file are created using Microsoft PowerPoint 2007 and above for Slide Show purpose. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.PresentationFileType.Odp
member.summary: Files with ODP extension represent presentation file format used by OpenOffice.org in the OASISOpen standard. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.PresentationFileType.Otp
member.summary: Files with .OTP extension represent presentation template files created by applications in OASIS OpenDocument standard format. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.PresentationFileType.Potx
member.summary: Files with .POTX extension represent Microsoft PowerPoint template presentations that are created with Microsoft PowerPoint 2007 and above. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.PresentationFileType.Pot
member.summary: Files with .POT extension represent Microsoft PowerPoint template files created by PowerPoint 97-2003 versions. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.PresentationFileType.Potm
member.summary: Files with POTM extension are Microsoft PowerPoint template files with support for Macros. POTM files are created with PowerPoint 2007 or above and contains default settings that can be used to create further presentation files. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.PresentationFileType.Pptm
member.summary: Files with PPTM extension are Macro-enabled Presentation files that are created with Microsoft PowerPoint 2007 or higher versions. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.PresentationFileType.Ppsm
member.summary: Files with PPSM extension represent Macro-enabled Slide Show file format created with Microsoft PowerPoint 2007 or higher. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.PresentationFileType.Fodp
member.summary: Files with FODP extension represent OpenDocument Flat XML Presentation. Presentation file saved in the OpenDocument format, but saved using a flat XML format instead of the .ZIP container used by standard .ODP files

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.ProjectManagementFileType.Mpt

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.ProjectManagementFileType.Mpp
member.summary: MPP is Microsoft Project data file that stores information related to project management in an integrated manner. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.ProjectManagementFileType.Mpx
member.summary: Microsoft Exchange File Format, is an ASCII file format for transferring of project information between Microsoft Project (MSP) and other applications that support the MPX file format such as Primavera Project Planner, Sciforma and Timerline Precision Estimating. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.ProjectManagementFileType.Xer
member.summary: The XER file format is a proprietary project file format used by Primavera P6 project planning and management application. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: T:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType
member.summary: Defines Spreadsheet documents. Includes the following file types: , , , , , , , , , , , , . Learn more about Spreadsheet formats here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Xls
member.summary: XLS represents Excel Binary File Format. Such files can be created by Microsoft Excel as well as other similar spreadsheet programs such as OpenOffice Calc or Apple Numbers. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Xlsx
member.summary: XLSX is well-known format for Microsoft Excel documents that was introduced by Microsoft with the release of Microsoft Office 2007. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Xlsm
member.summary: XLSM is a type of Spreadsheet files that support macros. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Xlsb
member.summary: XLSB file format specifies the Excel Binary File Format, which is a collection of records and structures that specify Excel workbook content. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Ods
member.summary: Files with ODS extension stand for OpenDocument Spreadsheet Document format that are editable by user. Data is stored inside ODF file into rows and columns. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Xltx
member.summary: XLTX file represents Microsoft Excel Template that are based on the Office OpenXML file format specifications. It is used to create a standard template file that can be utilized to generate XLSX files that exhibit the same settings as specified in the XLTX file. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Xlt
member.summary: Files with .XLT extension are template files created with Microsoft Excel which is a spreadsheet application which comes as part of Microsoft Office suite. Microsoft Office 97-2003 supported creating new XLT files as well as opening these. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Xltm
member.summary: The XLTM file extension represents files that are generated by Microsoft Excel as Macro-enabled template files. XLTM files are similar to XLTX in structure other than that the later doesn't support creating template files with macros. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Tsv
member.summary: A Tab-Separated Values (TSV) file format represents data separated with tabs in plain text format. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Csv
member.summary: Files with CSV (Comma Separated Values) extension represent plain text files that contain records of data with comma separated values. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Dif
member.summary: DIF stands for Data Interchange Format that is used to import/export spreadsheets data between different applications. These include Microsoft Excel, OpenOffice Calc, StarCalc and many others. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Sxc
member.summary: An XML based format used by OpenOffice and StarOffice

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.SpreadsheetFileType.Numbers

member.summary: FBX, FilmBox, is a popular 3D file format that was originally developed by Kaydara for MotionBuilder. It was acquired by Autodesk Inc in 2006 and is now one of the main 3D exchange formats as used by many 3D tools. FBX is available in both binary and ASCII file format. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: T:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.VideoFileType
member.summary: Defines Video documents Includes the following types: , , , , , , , Learn more about video formats here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.VideoFileType.Mp4
member.summary: MP4(short for MPEG-4 Part 14) is a file format based on ISO/IEC 14496-12:2004 that is based on QuickTime File Format but formally specifies support for Initial Object Descriptors (IOD) and other MPEG features. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.VideoFileType.Avi
member.summary: The AVI file format is an Audio Video multimedia container file format that was introduced by Microsoft. It holds the audio and video data created and compressed using several codecs (Coders/Decoders) such as XVid and DivX. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.VideoFileType.Flv
member.summary: FLV (Flash Video) is a container file format with the .flv extension. FLV is used to deliver audio/video content over the internet by using the Adobe Flash Player or Adobe Air. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.VideoFileType.Mkv
member.summary: MKV (Matroska Video) is a multimedia container similar to MOV and AVI format but it supports more than one audio and subtitle track in the same file. An MKV file is the Matroska multimedia container format used for video. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.VideoFileType.Mov
member.summary: MOV or QuickTime file format is a multimedia container which is developed by Apple: contains one or more tracks, each track holds a particular type of data i.e. Video, Audio, text, etc. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.VideoFileType.Webm
member.summary: A file with a .webm extension is a video file based on the open, royalty-free WebM file format. It has been designed for sharing video on the web and defines the file container structure including video and audio formats. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.VideoFileType.Wmv
member.summary: The Advanced Systems Format (ASF) is a digital multimedia container designed primarily for storing and transmitting media streams. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: T:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType
member.summary: Defines Word Processing files that contain user information in plain text or rich text format. A plain text file format contains unformatted text and no font or page settings etc. can be applied. In contrast, a rich text file format allows formatting options such as setting fonts type, styles (bold, italic, underline, etc.), page margins, headings, bullets and numbers, and several other formatting features. Includes the following file types: , , , , , , , , , , . . . Learn more about Word Processing formats here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Doc
member.summary: Files with .doc extension represent documents generated by Microsoft Word or other word processing documents in binary file format. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Docm
member.summary: DOCM files are Microsoft Word 2007 or higher generated documents with the ability to run macros. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Docx
member.summary: DOCX is a well-known format for Microsoft Word documents. Introduced from 2007 with the release of Microsoft Office 2007, the structure of this new Document format was changed from plain binary to a combination of XML and binary files. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Dot
member.summary: Files with .DOT extension are template files created by Microsoft Word to have pre-formatted settings for generation of further DOC or DOCX files. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Dotm
member.summary: A file with DOTM extension represents template file created with Microsoft Word 2007 or higher. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Dotx
member.summary: Files with DOTX extension are template files created by Microsoft Word to have pre-formatted settings for generation of further DOCX files. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Rtf
member.summary: Introduced and documented by Microsoft, the Rich Text Format (RTF) represents a method of encoding formatted text and graphics for use within applications. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Odt
member.summary: ODT files are type of documents created with word processing applications that are based on OpenDocument Text File format. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Ott
member.summary: Files with OTT extension represent template documents generated by applications in compliance with the OASIS' OpenDocument standard format. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Mobi
member.summary: The MOBI file format is one of the most widely used ebook file format. The format is an enhancement to the old OEB (Open Ebook Format) format and was used as proprietary format for Mobipocket Reader. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Txt
member.summary: A file with .TXT extension represents a text document that contains plain text in the form of lines. Learn more about this file format here.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Log
member.summary: A file with .LOG extension represents a text document that contains plain text in the form of lines.

member.name: F:GroupDocs.Conversion.FileTypes.WordProcessingFileType.Sql
member.summary: A file with .SQL extension represents a text document that contains sql.
